cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and text summarization. The use of Universal Transformer architecture and byte-pair encoding technique also suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Additionally, the task of headline generation involves information retrieval and ranking, which could place it in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks and deep learning techniques could also suggest that it belongs to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
